widgets_values:
Choose your face detector here, MediaPipe doesn't run on GPU and isn't as good at detecting, but is faster on CPU and has Apache 2.0 license.

Insightface can be run on GPU and is better at detecting, but it's model license is NON-COMMERCIAL
If you want to crop your driving video, use this as driving_images instead
Disabling rotate can produce less jittery results

How many frames you want to process.

The number of performance images should be the same or larger than the number of source images.
Connect this if you want to use the eye/lip retargeting mode

lip_zero (default false):
    true - closes lips as the resting pose. This will in theory produce better matching results
    false - leaves lips at the video's initial position

lip_zero_threshold (default 0.03):
    Controls the intensity of the change in the mouth's initial pose. 

stitching (default true):
    Enables or disables the stitch between the unchanged areas of the plate and the new animated head

delta_multiplier (default 1):
    Intensity of the new facial animation. 1 is a 1:1 match. Can go past 1 for exaggerated results. 

mismatch_method (default constant):
    ?

relative_motion_mode (default source_video_smoothed):
    Controls the head motion
    relative: 1:1 match
    source_video_smoothed: feels like it smooths out the motion and then applies it
    relative_roation_only: ?
    single frame: ?
    off: seems to disable facial anim and match head motion
    
expression_friendly (default false): works only with single source image
